///////////
Step to generate package.json
///////////
**NodeJs must be install in system
> Go inside the folder using cmd/terminal
> npm init
> answer all questions
> type yes

///////////
Step to instal package
///////////
> Go inside the folder using cmd/terminal
> npm i packagename

/////////////
step to generate react application
///////////
#window

##one time step in new laptop##
> open cmd as admin
> npm i -g create-react-app

## Every Time you want new app ##
> open cmd 
> go inside the folder
> create-react-app appname

> go inside the folder using cmd
> npm start

#mac

##one time step in new laptop##
> open terminal
> sudo npm i -g create-react-app

## Every Time you want new app ##
> open cmd 
> go inside the folder
> create-react-app appname

> go inside the folder using cmd
> npm start


////////////////////
> Functional
    > Display component
    > Dumb component
    > We don't write logic here
    > Cannot maintain State

> ClassComponent
    > Logical component
    > We can call api as well as Display
    > we can write logic
    > We can Maintain State

> HooksComponent



function add(a,b){
    var out = [a,b]
    return out
}


add(1,2)
[1,2]

////////////////
State
> act like a local variable
> any data interaction happen through state
> state can be updated (mutable)
> scope of state will be in same component only

Props
> is a way to transfer data
> data can be transfer from one nested component to other
> immutable (we cannot change data in props)

Map
filter
indexof

var a = [5,3,5,6,7,2,5,7,8,4,3,2]
a.map((data) => {return data*2})
[10, 6, 10, 12, 14, 4, 10, 14, 16, 8, 6, 4]

var a = [5,3,5,6,7,2,5,7,8,4,3,2]
a.filter((data) => {return data>5})
[6, 7, 7, 8]

var a = [0,1,2,3]
a.map((data) => {return data*2})
[0, 2, 4, 6]

a.filter((data) => {return data*2})
[1, 2, 3]

parent => child  (props)
child  => parent (props with function)

